Colombian Stocks: Grupo Nutresa, Coltejer, Almacenes Exito

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-07-01T20:23:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/colombian-stocks-grupo-nutresa-coltejer-almacenes-exito.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.1 percent to 14,075.58, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.4 percent to 1,707.03.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA CB),  Colombia ’s biggest food
producer, jumped 1.3 percent to 23,700 pesos. The company’s
offer to sell 25 million shares for 20,900 pesos each, which
began June 10, ends today.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , a Colombian clothing maker and
exporter, dropped 1.7 percent to 1.14 pesos. The U.S. Senate
Finance Committee was unable to consider trade pacts with
Colombia,  South Korea  and  Panama  yesterday because no
Republicans showed up, setting back efforts by President Barack
Obama and business groups to get the long-delayed accords
completed before a recess in August.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest publicly
traded retailer, fell 2.1 percent to 23,980 pesos, the lowest
level on a closing basis since Feb. 23. Exito said in a June 29
statement it may sell new shares to raise as much as $1.4
billion and purchase a stake in Uruguayan supermarkets from
majority shareholder Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
